Pushed me out of the immersion given Weber changes from 0 to 1 when the plot wants him to.

Reread it two times so I could be sure it wasn't my eyes or something but I don't really get why Weber states  If its to convey impatience or lording over the patient, I don't really get that from the overall character of Weber as he's somewhat of a blank slate filled with the goals of the Foundation itself. To protect coldly.

Maybe if I believed Weber wasn't just a foil for Dennis and had his own ambitions leading up to the tone shift, I would upvote it. As it stands, it's a solid piece but doesn't sit well with me in terms of narrative inconsistency.

