Cheers for picking up on those errors, I'll go in and edit them.

Thanks for the feedback on other things, but I've been working on this piece for months and I'm just happy to be done with it.

4504 is near other humanoids because he's being held at a humanoid containment site, and the frequent escapes are one of the points of the piece - if you put someone in a concrete box forever with nothing to do, they will a) spend every waking moment planning their escapes and b) hate you. One of the things I find inconsistent about other humanoid scps is that most of them do not have a history of attempting escapes. There's a reason humanoid SCP objects can't be classified as .

Weber is incompetent, but he's incompetent in a way that you can find in many clinics or prisons. He goes into his sessions with Dennis with an agenda. Instead of listening to Dennis and working on his problems, he's trying to force Dennis into a role so he can . That said, a lot of people think Weber's dialogue is flat, so if I was going to do something like this again I'd give it a few more reviews before posting.







